  "response": "Several celebrities have converted to Islam over the years. Here are some notable figures:\n\n1. **Muhammad Ali** - The legendary boxer converted to Islam in the 1960s and changed his name from Cassius Clay.\n2. **Cat Stevens (Yusuf Islam)** - The singer-songwriter converted to Islam in 1977 and adopted the name Yusuf Islam.\n3. **Janet Jackson** - The singer and actress converted to Islam after marrying Qatari businessman Wissam Al Mana in 2012.\n4. **Dave Chapelle** - The comedian converted to Islam during his early career.\n5. **Omarion** - The R&B singer is known to have converted to Islam.\n6. **Lupe Fiasco** - The rapper has spoken about his Islamic faith and lifestyle.\n7. **Bella Hadid** - The model has mentioned her appreciation for her Palestinian heritage and Muslim roots, though her exact religious practices have varied.\n8. **Mike Tyson** - The former heavyweight champion boxed has spoken about his conversion to Islam and has been vocal about his faith.\n\nPlease note that the beliefs and practices of individuals can change over time, and the public statements of these celebrities might reflect their personal journeys and experiences with faith.",
